# Cloudflare Pages response headers (F9D production hardening).
# app.feelflick.com is served by Cloudflare Pages (see public/_redirects), so this
# file — NOT vercel.json — is what reaches production. vercel.json mirrors these
# for the Vercel preview/deploy path.
#
# Only SAFE, non-breaking headers are enforced here. A Content-Security-Policy is
# intentionally deferred: the app uses inline `style=` pervasively (and an inline
# <style> in index.html), so any CSP must allow style-src 'unsafe-inline', and
# script-src needs care for the Cloudflare Insights beacon + Vite — see
# docs/production-observability-security-f9d.md for the draft report-only CSP.

/*
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), browsing-topics=()
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000
